org.jconfigurations.converters

Interface CollectionConfigurationConverter<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Superinterfaces:
    ConfigurationConverter<Collection<T>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseCollectionConfigurationConverter, ListConfigurationConverter, NoCollectionConfigurationConverter, SetConfigurationConverter
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface CollectionConfigurationConverter<T>
extends ConfigurationConverter<Collection<T>>
    CollectionConfigurationConverters are used by configurators to convert a configuration value into an instance of a Collection of type T. Default implementations for List and Set are already provided. Users may opt to implement their own converters and specify those via CollectionConfiguration.converter(). The CollectionFieldConverterFunction requires that implementations provide an accessible constructor that accepts two arguments: a ConfigurationConverter and the string delimiter. CollectionConfigurationConverters only act upon fields marked with CollectionConfiguration.
    Author:
    George Aristy
    See Also:
